author: app.com
title: Ferraro, Kaplan fuel Manalapan win over Freehold
text:
MORE Senior forward Arianna Ferraro had one goal and one assist, sophomore forward Ariella Kaplan added one goal and junior midfielder Mya Donnelly had an assist as the No. 7 Manalapan girls soccer team defeated Freehold, 2-0, in a Class A North game on Friday afternoon.
Ferraro now has 13 goals and eight assists this season while Kaplan had her sixth goal and Donnelly had her third assist. Manalapan junior goalie Ariel Kamen had four saves as the Braves (10-1, 9-1) won their seventh game in a row.
Freehold sophomore goalie Stephanie Moir made 16 saves for the Colonials (6-6-1, 5-5-1).
